The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 January is 32,051 (3,709.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 January, there were 4,473 new confirmed cases (517.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 January, there were 5,865 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 24% (1,392 fewer cases).
